strategy: Implement a three-phase approach: (1) Create a fully denormalized dimension CTE pre-joining all dimension tables with filters applied; (2) Join this dimension CTE once with store_sales in a single pas
what_failed:
Regression (0.94x): Consolidated the two separate scans of store_sales into a single pass by pre-joining all dimension tables into a dimensions CTE and using conditional aggregation with a filtered promotion subquery.
-- Expected speedup: 3-4x by eliminating duplicate fact table scan and enabling optimal join ordering.
why_it_failed: Split a simple OR condition (t_hour BETWEEN 10 AND 11 OR t_hour BETWEEN 16 AND 17) into UNION ALL of two separate web_sales scans. This doubles the fact table scan. DuckDB handles same-column OR ranges efficiently in a single scan — the UNION ALL adds materialization overhead with zero selectivity benefit.
